    {
      "id": "1b44750c-f3ba-8081-a81b-cad30b5e5e99",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The authors explore how the Contextual Bandit Algorithm can be used in a KT task to improve the quality of student support recommendations. The authors employ their algorithm in a simulated environment and see that features engineered using this algorithm result in better rewards than randomly selected student supports. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
